festival.introText:
The Noughty 90’s Festival returns to Waterhall in Brighton on Saturday 30th April 2022.

Boasting four huge stages of music, the biggest 00’s and 90’s bands, artists and DJ’s from around the world, funfair rides, a 90’s arcade, Retro Bars, an RnB Roller Disco, Gourmet Street Food, Exclusive VIP Area and so much more, this is the ULTIMATE throwback.
 
THE POP HITS STAGE
Bringing you the biggest and most loved pop and dance acts from the 00’s and 90’s. Put on your dancing shoes and get ready for the sing-a-longs!
 
Clockwork Orange STAGE
The House Classic Anthems and IBIZA Summer Vibes bringing you the biggest and best DJ’s from our era.
 
Garage Nation STAGE
Calling all UK Garage RAVERS! The heavy weights have arrived, bringing you the bangers Garage classics. This one goes out to the old skool!
 
AWOL - A Way of Life STAGE
Oi Oi!! All the whistles, all the horns! The undisputed legendary AWOL are here. Bringing you the Jungle and D&B Classics.
 
And let’s not forget about the R&B ROLLER DISCO. The home or old skool R&B and Hip Hop.
 
Line up coming soon...
 
 
Be sure to hit 'INTERESTED' to be the first to hear about our Line Up, Tickets and Stage Host Announcements!
 
https://www.facebook.com/events/453084622065907/
 
Follow us on Instagram and Twitter @noughty90sfest
 
Contact: info@noughty90sfest.co.uk
 
18+ only.
 
http://www.noughty90sfest.com

reviews.title: Review of Noughty 90's Festival Brighton 2022
reviews.body: Well organised and good variety off stages. Good to have a VIP option

reviews.title: Review of Noughty 90's Festival Brighton 2022
reviews.body: First Cardiff Noughty 90s,was a good 90s festival, the prices were a bit on the higher side but was a good event..

reviews.title: Review of Noughty 90's Festival Brighton 2022
reviews.body: Lovely atmosphere, lovely venue all great but the price was a complete rip off

reviews.title: Review of Noughty 90's Festival Brighton 2022
reviews.body: Great event. Could do with more advance details on the location and traffic arrangements. Food and drink obviously expensive as is the case at these events, however it was a sensible expensive and not a break the bank job! Look forward to returning soon!

faqs.question: Is there disabled access at Noughty 90's Festival?
faqs.answer: To receive a free carer ticket, please email info@noughty90sfest.co.uk to provide proof of PIP.
